description:
CRITICAL: better-sqlite3 fails when installed as dependency.

## Error
```
Error: Could not locate the bindings file.
Tried: .../better-sqlite3/build/better_sqlite3.node
```

## Root Cause
better-sqlite3 requires native compilation. When installed via npm as a dependency in another project, bindings may not compile.

## Implementation Options

### Option A: Add postinstall script (Simplest)
In `package.json`:
```json
{
  "scripts": {
    "postinstall": "cd node_modules/better-sqlite3 && npm run build-release"
  }
}
```

### Option B: Use prebuild-install
better-sqlite3 supports prebuilt binaries:
```json
{
  "dependencies": {
    "better-sqlite3": "^11.0.0"
  },
  "optionalDependencies": {
    "better-sqlite3-prebuilt": "^11.0.0"
  }
}
```

### Option C: Switch to sql.js (Pure JS - No native deps)
```bash
pnpm remove better-sqlite3
pnpm add sql.js
```
Requires rewrite of storage layer but eliminates native module issues.

### Option D: Lazy-load SQLite with fallback
```typescript
let db: Database | null = null;
try {
  const Database = require('better-sqlite3');
  db = new Database(path);
} catch (e) {
  console.warn('SQLite unavailable, using JSONL-only mode');
}
```

## Recommended
Try Option A first. If it fails across platforms, implement Option D (graceful degradation).

